  "prompt": "What are some of the funniest movies you've ever seen?",
  "response": "Humor is subjective, but here are some widely beloved and hilarious movies that many people consider laugh-out-loud funny:\n\n### Classic Comedies:\n1. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail** (1975) - Absurd, surreal humor from the legendary British comedy group.\n2. **Airplane!** (1980) - A slapstick spoof of disaster movies with non-stop jokes.\n3. **The Naked Gun** (1988) - Leslie Nielsen\u2019s deadpan comedy in a ridiculous cop spoof.\n4. **Some Like It Hot** (1959) - A timeless screwball comedy with Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, and Jack Lemmon.\n5. **Blazing Saddles** (1974) - Mel Brooks' outrageous Western satire.\n\n### Modern Comedies:\n1. **Bridesmaids** (2011) - A raunchy, heartfelt comedy about friendship and wedding chaos.\n2. **Superbad** (2007) - A coming-of-age teen comedy with outrageous humor.\n3. **The Hangover** (2009) - A wild, unpredictable bachelor party gone wrong.\n4. **Step Brothers** (2008) - Will Ferrell and John C. Reilly as 40-something stepbrothers acting like kids.\n5. **21 Jump Street** (2012) - A hilarious reboot of the classic TV show.\n\n### Quirky and Unique:\n1. **Napoleon Dynamite** (2004) - A cult classic with awkward, deadpan humor.\n2. **What We Do in the Shadows** (2014) - A mockumentary about vampire roommates.\n3. **The Big Lebowski** (1998) - The Coen Brothers' quirky, laid-back comedy about a slacker caught in a bizarre crime.\n4. **Ferris Bueller\u2019s Day Off** (1986) - A feel-good comedy about skipping school in style.\n\n### International Comedies:\n1. **Am\u00e9lie** (2001) - A whimsical French romantic comedy.\n2. **Shaun of the Dead** (2004) - A British zombie comedy with sharp wit.\n\nThese movies have stood the test of time or made a huge impact on comedy filmmaking. If you haven't seen any of them, they're absolutely worth checking out!",
